A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO PEER SUPPORT PROGRAMS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that parenting can be
2 challenging for anyone, but especially for parents and families
3 whose basic needs are not met. Parents and caregivers who lack
4 needed support may experience depression and mental health
5 challenges, intimate partner violence, child abuse and neglect,
6 and substance addiction. This in turn may cause early childhood
7 trauma for the children under their care.
8 The legislature further finds that each year in Hawaii,
9 close to six hundred children from birth to age five are
10 confirmed to be victims of child abuse and neglect, although the
11 actual number of cases may be as much as five times greater.
12 The legislature notes that half of all children in the child
13 welfare system are under the age of five. Child rearing
14 practices and handling parenting responsibilities made up the
15 majority of contributing factors to child abuse and neglect,
16 along with drug use. Child abuse and neglect impacts brain
17 development and is costly, with the total lifetime economic
