1 downstream interventions. Research has shown that investing in
2 the prenatal-to-five-year time period can save seven times in
3 downstream costs, including reducing costs associated with
4 treatment programs, child welfare programs, special education
5 programs, and incarceration.
6 The purpose of this Act is to support parents and
7 caregivers of children from birth to age five by appropriating
8 funds to the family health services division of the department
9 of health to establish and oversee peer-to-peer support
10 programs.
11 SECTION 2, There is appropriated out of the general
12 revenues of the State of Hawaii the sum of $860,000 or so much
13 thereof as may be necessary for fiscal year 2025-2026 and the
14 same sum or so much thereof as may be necessary for fiscal year
15 2026-2027 for the family health services division of the
16 department of health to establish and support peer-to-peer
17 support programs for families with children from birth to age
18 five, to be expended as follows:
19 (1) $200,000 for one full-time equivalent (1.0 FTE)
20 program specialist V position and one full-time
21 equivalent (1.0 FTE) program specialist IV position;
